In a speech given at the FBI National Academy graduation ceremony, President Trump expressed his support and gratitude for law enforcement officers in the United States. He praised the graduates for their dedication and courage, and emphasized the importance of showing respect and gratitude to police officers. Trump also spoke about the rise in violent crime in the country and called for stronger measures to protect law enforcement officers. He highlighted the need to address immigration issues and crack down on criminal gangs like MS-13. The President concluded by thanking the officers and their families for their sacrifices and service to the nation.